---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "80C Deductions Complete Guide: Save Up to ₹1.5 Lakh Tax";
const description = "Complete guide to Section 80C deductions. Learn about PPF, ELSS, NSC, home loan principal, life insurance, and other investments to save tax under Section 80C for FY 2024-25.";
const image = "/images/blogs/section-80c-deductions-guide.jpg";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} image={image}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-canvas dark:bg-primary">
    <main class="min-h-screen">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6 text-sm">
          <ol class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><a href="/" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Home</a></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-muted">/</span><a href="/blogs" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Blogs</a></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-muted">/</span><span class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-on-primary" aria-current="page">80C Deductions Guide</span></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <article class="prose max-w-none">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 dark:text-on-primary">80C Deductions Complete Guide: Save Up to ₹1.5 Lakh Tax</h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-body dark:text-muted">Last updated: July 2026 | 14 min read</p>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-body dark:text-muted">
            <p>Section 80C of the Income Tax Act is the most popular tax-saving section for Indian taxpayers. It allows deductions of up to ₹1.5 lakh in a financial year for specified investments and expenses. This comprehensive guide covers every aspect of Section 80C deductions, helping you maximize your tax savings for FY 2024-25.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">What is Section 80C?</h2>
            <p>Section 80C allows individuals and HUFs to claim deductions for certain investments and expenses. The total deduction available under Section 80C, 80CCC, and 80CCD(1) combined is limited to ₹1.5 lakh. This means you can invest in multiple instruments under these sections, but the total deduction cannot exceed ₹1.5 lakh.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Investments Eligible Under Section 80C</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Employee Provident Fund (EPF)</li>
              <li>Public Provident Fund (PPF)</li>
              <li>Equity Linked Savings Scheme (ELSS)</li>
              <li>National Savings Certificate (NSC)</li>
              <li>5-year fixed deposits with banks</li>
              <li>Life insurance premiums</li>
              <li>Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana (SSY)</li>
              <li>Home loan principal repayment</li>
              <li>Tuition fees for children (max 2 children)</li>
              <li>National Pension System (NPS) contribution</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Best 80C Investments for Different Risk Profiles</h2>
            <p><strong>For conservative investors:</strong> PPF, NSC, 5-year FD, and life insurance are ideal. PPF offers guaranteed returns with tax-free maturity. NSC provides fixed returns with interest eligible for 80C.</p>
            <p><strong>For moderate risk investors:</strong> ELSS funds offer the potential for higher returns with a relatively short lock-in period of 3 years. Historically, ELSS has delivered 12-15% annual returns over the long term.</p>
            <p><strong>For aggressive investors:</strong> NPS with equity allocation can provide market-linked returns along with the additional ₹50,000 deduction under Section 80CCD(1B).</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">80C Deduction Planning Tips</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Start investing early in the financial year to benefit from compounding</li>
              <li>Diversify across multiple instruments to balance risk and return</li>
              <li>Use ELSS for long-term wealth creation with tax benefits</li>
              <li>Claim home loan principal repayment under 80C</li>
              <li>Remember that EPF contributions automatically qualify</li>
              <li>Don't forget tuition fees for your children</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Investing in 80C at the last minute without proper planning</li>
              <li>Choosing ELSS just for tax saving without evaluating fund performance</li>
              <li>Not claiming EPF contributions</li>
              <li>Forgetting to claim tuition fees</li>
              <li>Investing in low-yield instruments for tax saving alone</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Conclusion</h2>
            <p>Section 80C offers a wide range of investment options to save tax while building wealth. Choose instruments based on your risk profile, investment horizon, and financial goals. Use our income tax calculator to estimate your tax savings under Section 80C.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
